Bye bye, John. Lovely to meet you.

18:04.640 --> 18:06.920
Sorry, bye bye.

18:06.920 --> 18:09.520
I didn't catch your name?
It's Marianne.

18:09.520 --> 18:12.680
Marianne, right.
You were at the lunch, weren't you?

18:12.680 --> 18:15.080
No, I'm a freelancer.

18:15.080 --> 18:18.120
I'm just doing some feature shifts.

18:18.120 --> 18:20.320
Sorry, Marianne!

18:20.320 --> 18:24.040
You were behind us just now
coming down the stairs, weren't you?

18:24.040 --> 18:27.240
So you heard
what we were talking about.

18:27.240 --> 18:31.680
But we were off the record so...
Well...very nice to meet you anyway.

18:36.720 --> 18:43.000
Shit. Shit. Hey! French Lieutenant's
woman, we're over here. Come on.

18:43.000 --> 18:44.800
What are you doing?
Marking out your territory?

18:44.800 --> 18:47.160
Welcome to the mother ship.

18:47.160 --> 18:48.680
I need some air.

18:48.680 --> 18:50.520
Ollie...open the door.

18:52.080 --> 18:54.080
She's not a post-match puker,
is she?

18:54.080 --> 18:55.760
Come on! What is it?

18:55.760 --> 19:00.000
Over there, there's a woman, with
red hair, woman on the phone. She
was behind me on the stairs.

19:00.000 --> 19:03.480
I thought she was off the record,
she was on the record,
so I need you to go over

19:03.480 --> 19:05.480
and take whatever was on
the record off the record.

19:05.480 --> 19:09.400
What...?
Don't be thick! For once just go
over there and just say it's off.

19:09.400 --> 19:13.400
Say whatever it was is off the
record. Go, now, run! All right!

19:13.400 --> 19:14.800
I don't know what she said.

19:18.960 --> 19:21.320
Yep.

19:21.320 --> 19:24.120
I'm going to miss my
wine-tasting again tonight.

19:25.680 --> 19:28.960
I expect you're probably
more a single malt man.

19:30.920 --> 19:33.440
I quite like her at times.

19:33.440 --> 19:36.000
For fuck's sake. Have we not
both got BlackBerries to check?

19:37.640 --> 19:42.360
Marion, I'm not threatening you,
but... What? Like I said,
I'm not threatening you...

19:42.360 --> 19:46.320
Usually the phrase,
"I'm not threatening you, but..."
is followed by a threat.

19:46.320 --> 19:48.480
I'm sorry, Malcolm.
I'm really sorry.

19:48.480 --> 19:52.240
Fuck's sake!

19:52.240 --> 19:55.800
Jesus Christ! Now we've got another

19:55.800 --> 19:59.400
fucking adjective to add to
fucking smug and glum, haven't we?

19:59.400 --> 20:02.040
Fucking retarded! Jesus!

20:02.040 --> 20:05.560
Do you not think it would be germane
to check who you're talking to?

20:05.560 --> 20:07.160
It's a fucking newspaper office.

20:07.160 --> 20:11.840
It's not a fucking sanatorium
for the fucking deaf, is it?
Are you so dense?

20:11.840 --> 20:14.960
I'm now going to have to run around
slapping badges on people.

20:14.960 --> 20:18.080
I'll put a big tick on some and
a big cross on others, so you know

20:18.080 --> 20:20.400
when to shut your gob
and when to open it!

20:20.400 --> 20:23.440
Jesus Christ! That would probably
confuse you as well, won't it?

20:23.440 --> 20:25.160
That'd be too confusing.

20:25.160 --> 20:28.520
You'll see the cross and think,
"X marks the spot".

20:28.520 --> 20:33.160
Better tell this little person
about the Prime Minister's
catastrophic erectile dysfunction.

20:33.160 --> 20:34.960
Oh, but not to worry, not to worry.

20:34.960 --> 20:36.840
You've sent Ollie over there...

20:36.840 --> 20:41.840
Fucking Ollie? He's a fucking
knitted scarf, that twat.
He's a balaclava.

20:41.840 --> 20:43.520
You're on very shaky legal ground.

20:43.520 --> 20:46.640
No, I'm really not. Am I? ..Oh.

20:46.640 --> 20:50.560
Look, the department's not
fit for purpose, really.

20:50.560 --> 20:52.280
No, it's not. Terri's quite bad...

20:52.280 --> 20:56.760
Not just Terri, I'm not going to
name names, but there's Robyn.
Robyn's shit.

20:56.760 --> 20:58.360
All right. Fuck off.

20:58.360 --> 21:01.840
I'm sure we can settle
this matter of...

21:01.840 --> 21:04.920
You were eavesdropping
on a private conversation?

21:06.440 --> 21:09.320
It was a public conversation.

21:09.320 --> 21:15.480
No, you think you're so clever
and you are so totally wanking with
the wrong crowd here, because...

21:15.480 --> 21:18.160
This man, right,
this man is the press.

21:18.160 --> 21:22.000
I mis-spoke and I mis-saw you.

21:22.000 --> 21:24.040
Nicola. Fuck. What've I done?

21:24.040 --> 21:26.040
D'you think this is going
to advance your career?

21:26.040 --> 21:28.120
At least my career's
got a trajectory,

21:28.120 --> 21:31.720
whereas yours is about to crash
head-on into a change of government.

21:31.720 --> 21:35.760
Don't you worry, because I can
still steer some fucking flaming
wreckage in your direction.

21:35.760 --> 21:39.680
Once it's printed,
I promise I'll come back to you
for reaction quote. How's that?

21:39.680 --> 21:43.280
Darling, I wouldn't fucking piss on
you if you were allergic to piss.

21:43.280 --> 21:46.000
On the you go. Walk the walk.

21:46.000 --> 21:47.760
Fuck right off. Go on.

21:47.760 --> 21:52.200
We'll live through this, won't we?
Nicola, I've got the list
whenever you're ready. I'm ready now.

21:52.200 --> 21:55.760
I can do it in reverse order like the
pop charts. How was meet the press?

21:55.760 --> 21:58.760
Not great. They didn't know
about the data loss, they do now.

21:58.760 --> 22:01.760
OK. Well, off the record,
they can't use any of it.

22:01.760 --> 22:04.760
No, I was ambushed by a
not-off-the-record journalist.

22:04.760 --> 22:06.720
Never mind! Onwards and upwards!

22:06.720 --> 22:08.960
Oh, fuck! From now on, none
of us let her out of our sight.

22:08.960 --> 22:11.280
She's not to be trusted.
Sorry, Minister. Terri?

22:11.280 --> 22:14.040
Yes? Where in the Civil Service
guidelines does it say that it's

22:14.040 --> 22:17.840
absolutely fine to leave
your minister alone
with a hostile journalist

22:17.840 --> 22:21.960
if you just can't be arsed
to walk down the stairs?
I'd already pressed the button.

22:21.960 --> 22:26.360
However, it was supposed
to be on Ollie's stick,
so he is the last man standing.

22:26.360 --> 22:32.080
Hey! At least I know how to use a
stick, Mr Floppy. Have you finished?
Well, no.

22:32.080 --> 22:36.560
I imagine I'm going to have to be
doing it over and over again until
you go on the fucking course.

22:36.560 --> 22:38.440
OK. Let's call a truce.

22:38.440 --> 22:41.040
Let's agree that nobody in this
room is going to be sacked, OK?

22:41.040 --> 22:44.360
For now. I've still got the original
list here, let's start with that.

22:44.360 --> 22:46.640
Top of the list is Kelly Peters. No.

22:46.640 --> 22:50.800
Why not? She's a very nice girl,
Kelly Peters. She's very kind.

22:50.800 --> 22:53.960
She often lends me hardbacks.
Terri, the Mail is on the phone.

22:53.960 --> 22:56.200
Christ.
Don't worry, I'll deal with it.

22:56.200 --> 22:58.600
I'll deal with it.

22:58.600 --> 23:00.160
Robyn?

23:00.160 --> 23:04.120
What? Yeah. No, absolutely not.
There are too many implications.

23:04.120 --> 23:07.120
We simply cannot go with the
idea of sacking Robyn. OK?

23:07.120 --> 23:10.480
Are you sleeping with her? What? No!

23:10.480 --> 23:13.680
Although every time he does see her
in his head he just hears...

23:13.680 --> 23:16.360
# Bam-chicka-bam-bam... #

23:16.360 --> 23:19.320
Ollie! It just seems to me that all
we'd be losing if we got rid of

23:19.320 --> 23:21.440
Robyn is somebody who makes
a week cup of tea.

23:21.440 --> 23:24.480
PHONE RINGS

23:21.440 --> 23:24.480
Shit. Malcolm. Hello.

23:24.480 --> 23:26.320
Get over here, now.

23:26.320 --> 23:30.200
It might be advisable to wear
brown trousers. And a shirt
the colour of blood.

23:32.480 --> 23:34.400
It has all gone HBO.

23:34.400 --> 23:40.720
I have got to go to Number Ten now.
Now? Need a coat and you, Terri.

23:40.720 --> 23:43.720
Really? Fuck shoes!

23:45.240 --> 23:47.080
Do you want me to come with you too?
Yes.

23:47.080 --> 23:50.600
Shit. OK, we're off.

23:50.600 --> 23:53.200
I'm wondering whether to
take the lift, no I can't.

23:53.200 --> 24:00.120
I just wanted to see to you
by the way of introductory remarks
that I'm extremely miffed about

24:00.120 --> 24:01.960
today's events.

24:01.960 --> 24:06.840
In my quest to try and make
you understand the level of my

24:06.840 --> 24:13.920
unhappiness, I'm likely to use
an awful lot of what we would call
violent sexual imagery.

24:13.920 --> 24:18.760
I just wanted to check
that neither of you would be
terribly offended by that.

24:18.760 --> 24:22.920
I could actually do without
the theatrics, Malcolm. Enough.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.160
E-fucking-nuff.

24:25.160 --> 24:28.680
You need to learn
to shut your fucking cave, right?

24:28.680 --> 24:33.800
Today, you have laid your first
big, fat egg of solid fuck.

24:33.800 --> 24:39.880
You took the data loss
media strategy and you ate it
with a lump of E-coli.

24:39.880 --> 24:42.800
Then you sprayed it out
of your arse at 300 mph.

24:42.800 --> 24:45.800
I simply made a mistake, Malcolm.

24:45.800 --> 24:48.280
You got on the record
and off the record mixed up.

24:48.280 --> 24:51.320
What would have happened if
George Martin had done that?

24:51.320 --> 24:53.800
There would be no
fucking Beatles, that's what.

24:53.800 --> 24:58.320
I don't give a fuck about that.
I've had to sit next to Paul
McCartney at fucking Chequers.

24:58.320 --> 25:01.360
The data loss wasn't my fault.

25:01.360 --> 25:04.640
I tell you what, it came out
pretty fast once you were
in there, didn't it?

25:04.640 --> 25:07.400
Which makes me wonder should
I just go and talk to the boss,

25:07.400 --> 25:09.320
should I tell him
I don't think she's up to the job.

25:09.320 --> 25:12.760
You said if he sacked me after a
week it looks like he's fucked up.

25:12.760 --> 25:19.160
But that was before, when your only
problem was a shit pun in a newspaper

25:19.160 --> 25:23.080
and a face like Dot Cotton
licking piss off a nettle.

25:23.080 --> 25:26.600
OK. I messed up. I messed up but...

25:26.600 --> 25:30.680
I will from now on listen to
every bit of advice you give me.

25:30.680 --> 25:35.280
I'll go on Question Time wearing
a push-up bra and a fez.

25:35.280 --> 25:38.680
I'll do the hustings on stilts
if that is what

25:38.680 --> 25:41.560
you tell me the strategy is because
you know about that stuff, Malcolm.

25:41.560 --> 25:45.600
I know that. It's just that I've got
things that I want to do, all right?

25:45.600 --> 25:49.200
Of course you do.
You want to sort out rocking horses?

25:49.200 --> 25:51.960
No. The Mail have the
mother lode on this, right.

25:51.960 --> 25:55.720
That means there is a way
through this for us but it entails

25:55.720 --> 26:01.560
you, my dear, eating a complete
concrete mixer full of humble pie.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.240
What's the strategy?

26:05.120 --> 26:08.960
The Kraken awakes. No, it's just that
this is the first bit of the meeting

26:08.960 --> 26:13.240
there hasn't been without expletives
and fezzes and stilts
and tea bagging.

26:13.240 --> 26:15.600
This is the bit that
relates to media management.

26:15.600 --> 26:17.640
I didn't say anything
about tea bagging.

26:17.640 --> 26:20.120
D'you know what that is?

26:20.120 --> 26:21.920
Not really, no.

26:21.920 --> 26:24.280
I'm told it's unpleasant.
Who do you want me to call?

26:24.280 --> 26:26.680
The Mail. Get them in.

26:26.680 --> 26:30.600
OK, Cheeky Girls, back on tour.

26:30.600 --> 26:32.760
Love your work.

26:32.760 --> 26:35.800
This is Marianne from the Mail.

26:35.800 --> 26:37.600
I've told you
who I want you to fire.

26:37.600 --> 26:41.040
I want you to do it,
not me, because I'm

26:41.040 --> 26:43.840
relatively popular around here and
frankly you've got nothing to lose.

26:47.040 --> 26:50.520
This is it, Robyn.
This is me true to my word.

26:50.520 --> 26:53.640
Andrew, mate. Sorry, nothing
personal. Clear your desk and go.

26:53.640 --> 26:55.400
Please don't hit me,
I'm wearing glasses.

26:55.400 --> 27:01.840
I'd just like to say to your readers
that the person responsible is being

27:01.840 --> 27:05.840
fast-tracked to the dole
queue as fast as her kitten heels
will carry her.

27:05.840 --> 27:07.480
You need to leave your badge.

27:07.480 --> 27:09.160
Security. Stick it.

27:09.160 --> 27:12.880
Andrew, please don't
take it like this, please.

27:12.880 --> 27:16.760
We're going to sort this mess out.
Andrew!

27:16.760 --> 27:20.640
What is going on out there?

27:20.640 --> 27:22.840
That was...

27:22.840 --> 27:25.120
the person responsible.

27:25.120 --> 27:28.080
Didn't you say something
about kitten heels?

27:28.080 --> 27:31.280
It's never a pretty business
but he made mistakes.

27:31.280 --> 27:34.120
And he had to go.

27:34.120 --> 27:36.760
Ollie, perhaps you could
show Marianne to the lifts.

27:36.760 --> 27:41.240
Actually I thought I might
take the stairs and see what else
I can pick up on my way out.

27:41.240 --> 27:43.160
Very funny.

27:43.160 --> 27:45.080
Hi, Nicola.

27:46.400 --> 27:48.360
Nicola, you all right?

27:48.360 --> 27:50.280
Robyn, could you get me some tea?

27:50.280 --> 27:52.400
Now.

27:53.680 --> 27:55.640
Um...bad moment?

27:55.640 --> 27:58.600
You sacked the wrong person.

27:58.600 --> 28:01.080
They're all bad moments.
Glenn, how is she?

28:01.080 --> 28:04.160
She looks so glum.

28:04.160 --> 28:06.480
She looks like I feel
when I visit Sheffield.

28:08.200 --> 28:12.560
The Guardian didn't like us
going on the record to the Mail.
I did try and spin it.

28:12.560 --> 28:14.240
I got them to take "frowny" out.

28:14.240 --> 28:17.440
No, you didn't, that is
the second adjective.

28:17.440 --> 28:22.200
Well, I did do something.
Nicola Murray, looking glum
and frowny, was overheard...

28:22.200 --> 28:26.720
Glenn, mate. What would you do if you
found that a dongle that everybody

28:26.720 --> 28:32.280
thought was lost was right at
the bottom of your second-best bag?

28:32.280 --> 28:34.560
I don't think we'd want it back.

28:34.560 --> 28:37.880
One of her gems is a plan
to outlaw plastic toys.

28:37.880 --> 28:40.560
Right now, Ollie, Nicola hates us.

28:40.560 --> 28:44.560
If she knew we'd found it,
she'd start laughing.

28:44.560 --> 28:48.960
Hating is better then laughing.
Trust me.

28:48.960 --> 28:51.560
Why anyone would want a brand her
a killjoy or sourpuss is beyond us.

28:51.560 --> 28:53.680
That's it, "sourpuss".

28:53.680 --> 28:59.240
They wanted to put "sour",
I suggested the puss. Morning.

28:59.240 --> 29:04.600
I'll see if I can find
a hammer and some acid.
